The martar run: One player gets buffed to the gills and sowed, while the rest of the raid waits near the gnome vendor. This player pays a lower lvl Freeport lover to man the doors of the militia house to keep them open. He runs up to Lucan, smacks him, and runs like mad out of the militia house towards the raid party. The raid party is split into two groups: the KOS group is against the wall, and the non KOS group is away from aggro range from the KOS group. Once the 'puller' reaches the non KOS group, they start hailing Lucan like crazy while the puller zones. After a bunch of hails, the four million other guards will return to their posts and only Lucan will remain. This is when the KoS group will join and Lucan can be taken down.<br>
<br>
The sure fire KOS maker: Everone inviso's (if KOS) or goes to the NFP zone, still in WFP. The guards are pulled one at a time by a puller that isnt KOS. He remains non KOS by zoning right before every guard kill to maintain his non KOS status. All the guards around Lucan are cleared, then finally Lucan. This is the most fun IMO (but Im KOS /shrug) This approach can also be done with a KOS Monk/SK, provided he is high enough lvl to single pull the guards with an arrow/spell.<br>
Hope this helps you out some.<br>
